legacy.full_text: The Southern Clan Confucius Family Temple in Quzhou, Zhejiang, is one of the 3 remaining Confucius Family Temples in China. legacy.full_text: Kuzhu tofu is a specialty of Zhejiang, made from fresh soybean milk by adding kuzhu leaves for soaking, and then slowly simmering and steaming the soaked soybean milk to form a solidified bean curd. It is dark brown in color and very tender and smooth in the mouth. #YummyZhejiang https://t.co/FdNsBT9rl2

legacy.full_text: The Donghu Park in Linhai City is known as "mini West Lake". The pavilion in the center is a 3-story pavilion with 8 sides with flying eaves and curved corners. It is rich in ancient style by the zig-zag bridges to connect all pavilions with water reflections. #AmazingZhejiang https://t.co/9RiAvp0DhV
